ProtoResult:
. "Suppose that $f$ is infinitely differentiable on an 
   interval $I$ and $ \lim_{n\to\infty}\frac{r^n}{ 
   n!}\|f^{(n)}\|_I=0. $ Then, if $x_0\in I^0$ the Taylor 
   series $$ \sum^\infty_{n=0}\frac{f^{(n)}(x_0)}{ n!} 
   (x-x_0)^n $$ converges uniformly to $f$ on $$ I_r=I\cap 
   [x_0-r,x_0+r]. $$"
